{"id": 6426, "title": "Ticket #6426: RemoteUserCpu never updated in history file", "description": "<blockquote>\nFNAL reports that <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=RemoteUserCpu\" title=\"Remote User Cpu\">RemoteUserCpu</a></span> and <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=RemoteSysCpu\" title=\"Remote Sys Cpu\">RemoteSysCpu</a></span> for all jobs is correctly reported in the user log, but both are always zero in the history file.\n\n<p>Investigation reveals that the classad parsing optimization work we did for the 8.7.0 release shortcutted over some of the dirty attribute tracking.  This means that real-valued attributes that change over lifetime of a classad are never marked dirty, so the shadow doesn't think they are changed, and doesn't send them to the schedd for permanent storage.\n\n</p><p>This dirty tracking code is also used in the job router and the gridmanager, we're looking at whether this breaks them as well.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2017-Oct-25 16:39:03 by tim:</em> <br/>\n\n<strong>Doc review:</strong> complete</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2017-Oct-27 07:06</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/ea5bd6047f72f0893fd600c7e2ebd7d4e788d56a\">[52682]</a></span>: Transplant version history for <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=6426\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('6426'); return false;\" title=\"RemoteUserCpu never updated in history file\">#6426</a></span>  (By Tim Theisen )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2017-Oct-24 17:03</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/d30036ac1ab4fb9295fe8bcab43c3a727d45ed41\">[52647]</a></span>: Document <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=6426\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('6426'); return false;\" title=\"RemoteUserCpu never updated in history file\">#6426</a></span>  (By Greg Thain )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2017-Oct-04 11:07</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/68f99bf0c4f210f8cc665eddaea0d7657f430cfa\">[52475]</a></span>: Allow <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=RemoteUserCpu\" title=\"Remote User Cpu\">RemoteUserCpu</a></span> and <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=RemoteSysCpu\" title=\"Remote Sys Cpu\">RemoteSysCpu</a></span> to be written to history file <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=6426\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('6426'); return false;\" title=\"RemoteUserCpu never updated in history file\">#6426</a></span> The classad dirty attribute tracking code was broken, which meant that changes to these value would not be seen as changes and thus not written.  (By Greg Thain )</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "type": "defect", "last_change": "2017-Oct-25 16:39", "status": "resolved", "created": "2017-Oct-04 10:37", "fixed_version": "2017-Oct-04 10:37", "broken_version": "v080700", "priority": "1", "subsystem": "", "assigned_to": "gthain", "derived_from": "", "creator": "gthain", "rust": "", "customer_group": "fermi", "visibility": "public", "notify": "", "due_date": ""}